    <p>The ed­i­tor of The On­line Ci­ti­zen (TOC) said he did not take down an ar­ti­cle con­tain­ing po­ten­tially li­bel­lous al­le­ga­tions about Prime Min­is­ter Lee Hsien Loong be­cause it was PM Lee’s press sec­re­tary who sent him a let­ter of de­mand in­stead of his lawyers. He said another fac­tor was the let­ter be­ing re­leased to the me­dia on the same day.</p>


